#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:3
#: 1c817417e4e344ffa5688341745431d7
msgid "Dom0 secure updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:7
#: 39c517f2766e4b7ebe7dae27d0d7993f
msgid "Reasons for Dom0 updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:10
#: 131f9474c66e4f64bc8b3cd42fb2a4ef
msgid ""
"Normally there should be few reasons for updating software in Dom0. This "
"is because there is no networking in Dom0, which means that even if some "
"bugs will be discovered e.g. in the Dom0 Desktop Manager, this really is "
"not a problem for Qubes, because all the third-party software running in "
"Dom0 is not accessible from VMs or network in any way. Some exceptions to"
" the above include: Qubes GUI daemon, Xen store daemon, and disk back-"
"ends (we plan to move the disk backends to untrusted domain in Qubes "
"2.0). Of course we believe this software is reasonably secure and we hope"
" it will not need patching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:12
#: 18b4ce2b8b1d4126a5b728dca5c1a8bc
msgid ""
"However, we anticipate some other situations when updating Dom0 software "
"might be required:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:14
#: 50e89a5ec2be40c2aa0048e47ebbbea7
msgid "Updating drivers/libs for new hardware support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:16
#: 2a75ff71c3ba4691892cfbd3f8c81d1d
msgid "Correcting non-security related bugs (e.g. new buttons for qubes manager)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:18
#: b120189e55c148b6aaed7b8dbe992bec
msgid "Adding new features (e.g. GUI backup tool)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:23
#: 9085ee6e4d104730ad525f610fc438d2
msgid "Problems with traditional network-based update mechanisms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:26
#: f837631fb9d34d2187edaa399b5045ba
msgid ""
"Dom0 is the most trusted domain on Qubes OS, and for this reason we "
"decided to design Qubes in such a way that Dom0 is not connected to any "
"network. In fact only certain domains can be connected to a network via "
"so-called network domains. There can also be more than one network "
"domain, e.g. in case the user is connected to more than one physically or"
" logically separated networks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:29
#: 806d316c8ccf4595ac75e0872f34a4d9
msgid "Secure update mechanism we use in Qubes (starting from Beta 2)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:32
#: 2b3ab47b4dc64a918ffcc123c78f0278
msgid ""
"Keeping Dom0 not connected to any network makes it hard, however, to "
"provide updates for software in Dom0. For this reason we have come up "
"with the following mechanism for Dom0 updates, which minimizes the amount"
" of untrusted input processed by Dom0 software:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:34
#: f1e81b2d03484619a0c4219297b505f9
msgid ""
"The update process is initiated by `qubes-dom0-update script "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-admin-"
"linux/blob/release2/dom0-updates/qubes-dom0-update>`__, running in Dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:36
#: 4c8c14b2fccc4072920a19605b00ef7a
msgid ""
"Updates (``*.rpm`` files) are checked and downloaded by UpdateVM, which "
"by default is the same as the firewall VM, but can be configured to be "
"any other, network-connected VM. This is done by `qubes-download-"
"dom0-updates.sh script <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-agent-"
"linux/blob/release2/misc/qubes-download-dom0-updates.sh>`__ (this script "
"is executed using qrexec by the previously mentioned qubes-dom0-update). "
"Note that we assume that this script might get compromised and fetch "
"maliciously compromised downloads – this is not a problem as Dom0 "
"verifies digital signatures on updates later. The downloaded rpm files "
"are placed in a ``/var/lib/qubes/dom0-updates`` directory on UpdateVM "
"filesystem (again, they might get compromised while being kept there, "
"still this isn’t a problem). This directory is passed to yum using the "
"``--installroot=`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:38
#: 283d1f0e94124c0f8621f10ab74fddbd
msgid ""
"Once updates are downloaded, the update script that runs in UpdateVM "
"requests an RPM service `qubes.ReceiveUpdates <https://github.com/QubesOS"
"/qubes-core-admin-"
"linux/blob/release2/dom0-updates/qubes.ReceiveUpdates>`__ to be executed "
"in Dom0. This service is implemented by `qubes-receive-updates script "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-admin-"
"linux/blob/release2/dom0-updates/qubes-receive-updates>`__ running in "
"Dom0. The Dom0’s qubes-dom0-update script (which originally initiated the"
" whole update process) waits until qubes-receive-updates finished."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:40
#: f6ca4f55511d40c9b555a126cd70cd87
msgid ""
"The qubes-receive-updates script processes the untrusted input from "
"Update VM: it first extracts the received ``*.rpm`` files (that are sent "
"over qrexec data connection) and then verifies digital signature on each "
"file. The qubes-receive-updates script is a security-critical component "
"of the Dom0 update process (as is the `qfile-dom0-unpacker.c "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-admin-"
"linux/blob/release2/dom0-updates/qfile-dom0-unpacker.c>`__ and the rpm "
"utility, both used by the qubes-receive-updates for processing the "
"untrusted input)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:42
#: ed3bf4c1e2b9467a90597d6f01e410b4
msgid ""
"Once qubes-receive-updates finished unpacking and verifying the updates, "
"the updates are placed in ``qubes-receive-updates`` directory in Dom0 "
"filesystem. Those updates are now trusted. Dom0 is configured (see "
"/etc/yum.conf in Dom0) to use this directory as a default (and only) `yum"
" repository <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-admin-"
"linux/blob/release2/dom0-updates/qubes-cached.repo>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:44
#: 02126abd79ce4c75a4964ae62a73b670
msgid ""
"Finally, qubes-dom0-update runs ``yum update`` that fetches the RPMs from"
" qubes-cached repo and installs them as usual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:47
#: 1fc44f8c5ec940138f9da41258fc8ae7
msgid "Security benefit of our update mechanism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/dom0-secure-updates.rst:50
#: b7ff21c00335448ea755704fcb7b4422
msgid ""
"The benefit of the above scheme is that one doesn’t need to trust the "
"TCP/IP stack, the HTTP stack, and wget implementation in order to safely "
"deliver and install updates in Dom0. One only needs to trust a few "
"hundred lines of code as discussed above, as well as the rpm utility for "
"properly checking digital signature (but this is required in any update "
"scheme)."
msgstr ""

